# SDLC Workflow

> This is the enforced process for this repo. Do not skip phases. Each phase gates the next.

## The Loop

```
NEW FEATURE/REQUEST
       ↓
   1. GRILL          — reach common ground before touching code
       ↓
   2. SPEC           — formalize what was agreed (/spec)
       ↓
   3. PLAN           — architecture + design review (/autoplan)
       ↓
   4. BUILD          — implement
       ↓
   5. REVIEW         — catch bugs before shipping (/review)
       ↓
   6. TEST           — verify in browser (/qa)
       ↓
   7. SHIP           — PR + tests + docs (/ship)
       ↓
   8. CAPTURE        — session file auto-created by hook
```

---

## Phase 1: GRILL (mandatory gate)

**Trigger:** User describes something new to build, or there is no session doc for this feature yet.

**How:** Use `/grill-me` or `/grill-with-docs` to reach common ground before any code is written.

- Ask one question at a time.
- Provide your recommended answer for each question.
- Resolve dependencies between decisions one by one.
- Do NOT proceed to Phase 2 until you have explicit agreement on: (1) what is being built, (2) what is out of scope, (3) why now.

**If user says "just build it" or "skip grilling":** Ask one clarifying question minimum — scope and out-of-scope. Then proceed.

---

## Phase 2: SPEC (/spec)

Turn the grilling outcome into a precise, executable spec.

```
/spec
```

- Five phases: why → scope → technical (reads codebase) → draft → file.
- Blocks below 7/10 quality score.
- Archives to `.gstack/projects/*/specs/` for recall.
- `--execute` spawns implementation in a fresh worktree.

---

## Phase 3: PLAN (/autoplan)

Run the full review pipeline on the spec before writing code.

```
/autoplan
```

- Runs CEO → design → eng review automatically.
- Surfaces only taste decisions for your approval.
- Writes a design doc that feeds all downstream skills.

---

## Phase 4: BUILD

Implement against the approved plan. Use `/careful` or `/guard` for production-touching work.

Check the graph before touching god nodes:
```
/graphify query "CONCEPT"
```

God nodes are listed in `main.mdc`. Changes to them ripple everywhere.

---

## Phase 5: REVIEW (/review)

```
/review
```

- Finds bugs that pass CI but blow up in production.
- Auto-fixes obvious issues. Flags completeness gaps.
- Use `/codex` for an independent second opinion from a different model.

---

## Phase 6: TEST (/qa)

```
/qa
```

- Opens a real browser, clicks through flows.
- Auto-generates regression tests for every fix.
- Use `/qa-only` for a report without code changes.

---

## Phase 7: SHIP (/ship)

```
/ship
```

- Syncs main, runs tests, audits coverage, opens PR.
- Auto-invokes `/document-release` to keep docs current.
- Bootstraps test framework if project has none.

---

## Phase 8: CAPTURE (automatic)

The `on-session-end.sh` hook fires automatically at agent stop.

- Creates `sessions/YYYY-MM-DD-N.md` with changed files.
- Appends row to `memory.md` index.
- Runs graphify incremental AST update in background.

**Your job after the hook fires:** Append `## Decisions` to the session file. Caveman style. 3-5 bullets. The "why", not the "what".

---

## Available gstack skills

```
/office-hours       start here — reframes the problem before planning
/spec               vague intent → precise executable spec
/autoplan           full review pipeline (CEO + design + eng)
/plan-ceo-review    challenge scope and find the 10-star product
/plan-eng-review    lock architecture, data flow, diagrams, edge cases
/plan-design-review rate design dimensions 0-10, interactive
/review             staff engineer review — bugs that pass CI
/codex              second opinion from OpenAI Codex (different model)
/qa                 real browser QA, fixes bugs, generates regression tests
/ship               sync → test → PR
/land-and-deploy    merge → CI → verify in production
/retro              weekly team retro with per-person breakdowns
/learn              manage what gstack learned — review, prune, export
/careful            warn before destructive commands
/guard              /careful + /freeze — max safety for prod work
/freeze             lock edits to one directory while debugging
/investigate        root-cause debugging — Iron Law: no fixes without investigation
/document-release   update all docs to match what just shipped
```

---

## Memory layers (read before architectural changes)

| Layer | What it contains | When to read |
|-------|-----------------|--------------|
| `main.mdc` | Architecture + god nodes (graphify) | Always — auto-loaded |
| `memory.md` | Index of all sessions | Before architectural changes |
| `sessions/` | Per-session caveman decisions | When you need the "why" for a past choice |
| `/learn` | gstack's cross-session learnings | Before starting a feature in familiar territory |
| `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` | Full graph audit with surprising connections | Before touching god nodes |
